cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper describes a multi-GPU implementation of the XGBoost library for gradient boosting, which is a popular machine learning technique used for classification and regression tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses data compression techniques and end-to-end GPU parallelism, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the use of decision trees and feature quantisation could relate to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), respectively.
